}

             childlink = 0; // prevents collapse effect when clicking on child link in expanded nav
        });

        $(this).parent().keydown(function(e){ // Jamie Johnson
            if(childlink!=0) {
                if(currentItem.is(":hidden")){
                if(e.keyCode=='39') { // right arrow expands
                    currentItem.toggle();
                }
                }
                if(currentItem.is(":visible")){
                if(e.keyCode=='37') { // left arrow collapses
                    currentItem.toggle();
                }
                }
                /* start arrow control */
                if(currentItem.is(":hidden")) { 
                    // arrow sideways 
                    currentItem.parent().css('background','url(//www.jmu.edu/jmucmsfiles/images/sidebar-side-arrow-gold.png)');                     
                    currentItem.parent().css('background-repeat','no-repeat'); 
                    currentItem.parent().css('background-position',navbgpos);

                    currentItem.parent().css('background-repeat','no-repeat'); 
                    currentItem.parent().css('background-position',navbgpos);

            }

<script language="javascript" type="text/javascript">
var mycookie=0;
function getCookie(c_name)
{
if (document.cookie.length>0)
  {
  c_start=document.cookie.indexOf(c_name + "=")
  if (c_start!=-1)
    { 
    c_start=c_start + c_name.length+1 
    c_end=document.cookie.indexOf(";",c_start)
    if (c_end==-1) c_end=document.cookie.length
    return unescape(document.cookie.substring(c_start,c_end))
    } 
  }
return ""
}

function setCookie(c_name,value,expiredays)
{
var exdate=new Date()
exdate.setDate(exdate.getDate()+expiredays)
document.cookie=c_name+ "=" +escape(value)+
((expiredays==null) ? "" : ";expires="+exdate.toGMTString())
}

function checkCookie()
{
gotit=getCookie('gotit');
if(isNaN(gotit)){gotit=0;setCookie('gotit',gotit,365)}
gotit=gotit*1; if(gotit>=storyqty){gotit=storyqty-1;setCookie('gotit',gotit,365)}

if (gotit!=null && gotit!="")
    { 
        // use the image
    }
else 
  {
  gotit=0; // set for first image
  if (gotit!=null && gotit!="")
    {
    setCookie('gotit',gotit,365)
    }
  }
}

checkCookie();

from urllib import request
import json
from pprint import pprint


census_api_key = '7c5aa9e94ec33a71064b55eaabe7fafe62bf7a0a' #get your key from https://api.census.gov/data/key_signup.html


url_str = 'https://api.census.gov/data/2016/acs/acs5?get=B01001_001E,B01001_002E,NAME&for=county:*&in=state:51&key='+census_api_key # create the url of your census data

response = request.urlopen(url_str) # read the response into computer

html_str = response.read().decode("utf-8") # convert the response into string

pop_max=0
# male_max=0
county_max=''
if (html_str):
    json_data = json.loads(html_str) # convert the string into json
    print (json_data[0])
    for v1,v2,name,state,county in json_data[1:]:
        if pop_max< int(v1):
            pop_max = int(v1)
            county_max = name
            
    print(pop_max)
    print(county_max)

from urllib import request
import json
from pprint import pprint


census_api_key = '7c5aa9e94ec33a71064b55eaabe7fafe62bf7a0a' #get your key from https://api.census.gov/data/key_signup.html


url_str = 'https://api.census.gov/data/2016/acs/acs5?get=B01001_001E,B01001_002E,NAME&for=county:*&in=state:51&key='+census_api_key # create the url of your census data

response = request.urlopen(url_str) # read the response into computer

html_str = response.read().decode("utf-8") # convert the response into string

pop_max=0
male_max=0
ratio_max= 0
county_max=''
if (html_str):
    json_data = json.loads(html_str) # convert the string into json
    print (json_data[0])
    for v1,v2,name,state,county in json_data[1:]:
        if ratio_max< (int(v2)/int(v1)):
            ratio_max = (int(v2)/int(v1))
            county_max = name
            
    print(ratio_max)
    print(county_max)
